load the dataset

d <- read_csv('data/nllb_sythetic.csv') %>% 
    mutate(dir = if_else(lang %in% c('pizza  crossiant', 'pizza  banana', 'pizza  grape'), 'pizza to other', 'other to pizza')) %>%
    mutate(lang = factor(lang, rev(c("pizza  banana", "pizza  grape", "pizza  crossiant", "banana  pizza",  "grape  pizza",  "crossiant  pizza") )))

compute mean and sd

d_summary <- 
d %>% group_by(lang, cosine, metric, direction, mean, sd, dir) %>% 
  summarise(mean_rep = mean(value), sd_rep = sd(value))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'lang', 'cosine', 'metric', 'direction',
## 'mean', 'sd'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
head(d_summary)
lang cosine metric direction mean sd dir mean_rep sd_rep
crossiant pizza 0.85 metric1 A B 0.892 0.046 other to pizza 0.8925034 0.0551083
crossiant pizza 0.85 metric1 B A 0.855 0.065 other to pizza 0.8545759 0.0784884

visualize mean and add p values

p1 <- d_summary %>% 
ggplot() +
  geom_path(aes(x = mean_rep, y = lang, color = direction, group = interaction(dir, direction)), linewidth = 1.2, alpha = .4) +
  geom_point(aes(x = mean_rep, y = lang, color = direction)) +
  geom_text(p_values, mapping = aes(x = 0.95, y = lang, label = paste0('p = ', p_formatted)), size = 3) + 
  facet_grid(cosine ~ metric, scale = 'free_x') + 
  scale_color_brewer(palette = 'Set1') +
  theme_ggdist()  + theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(linewidth=.3))
p1

uncerainty vis

just add standard deviation

p2 <- d_summary %>% 
ggplot() +
  geom_segment(aes(x = mean_rep - sd_rep, xend = mean_rep +  sd_rep, y = lang, yend = lang, color = direction)) +
  # geom_path(aes(x = mean_rep, y = lang, color = direction, group = direction), size = 1.2, alpha = .4) +
  geom_point(aes(x = mean_rep, y = lang, color = direction)) +
  geom_text(p_values, mapping = aes(x = 0.95, y = lang, label = p_formatted), size = 3) + 
  facet_grid(cosine ~ metric, scale = 'free') + 
  scale_color_brewer(palette = 'Set1') + 
  theme_ggdist()

p2

add CIs

p3 <- d_summary %>% 
ggplot() +
  geom_segment(aes(x = mean_rep - 1.96 * sd_rep / sqrt(N), xend = mean_rep + 1.96 * sd_rep / sqrt(N), y = lang, yend = lang, color = direction)) +
  geom_path(aes(x = mean_rep, y = lang, color = direction, group = interaction(dir, direction)), linewidth = .3, alpha = .4) +
  geom_point(aes(x = mean_rep, y = lang, color = direction)) +
  # geom_text(p_values, mapping = aes(x = 0.95, y = lang, label = p_formatted), linewidth = 3) + 
  facet_grid(cosine ~ metric, scale = 'free_x') + 
  scale_color_brewer(palette = 'Set1') + xlab('')  + 
  theme_ggdist() + theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(linewidth=.3))

p3

plot all data

d %>% 
  filter(metric == 'metric1') %>%
  ggplot() + 
  geom_point(aes(x = value, y = lang), alpha = .1) + 
  facet_wrap(cosine ~ .) + 
  scale_color_brewer(palette = 'Set1') + 
  theme_ggdist()

plot density plot

d %>% 
  filter(metric == 'metric1') %>%
  ggplot() + 
  stat_slab(aes(x = value, y = lang, fill = direction), alpha = .2) + 
  facet_wrap(cosine ~ .) + 
  scale_color_brewer(palette = 'Set1') + 
  theme_ggdist()

plot dot plot

d %>% 
  filter(metric == 'metric1') %>%
  ggplot() + 
  stat_dots(aes(x = value, y = lang, fill = direction), alpha = .5, quantiles = 50) + 
  facet_wrap(cosine ~ .) + 
  scale_color_brewer(palette = 'Set1') + 
  theme_ggdist()

plot gradient intervals

d %>% 
  filter(metric == 'metric1') %>%
  ggplot() + 
  stat_dist_gradientinterval(aes(x = value, y = lang), point_interval = NULL) + 
  facet_wrap(cosine ~ .) + 
  scale_color_brewer(palette = 'Set1') + 
  theme_ggdist()

plot discrete gradient intervals

d %>% 
  filter(metric == 'metric1') %>%
  ggplot() + 
  stat_interval(aes(x = value, y = lang)) + 
  facet_wrap(cosine ~ .) + 
  scale_color_brewer(palette = 'Blues') + 
  theme_ggdist()

draw ribbons + CIs

p3 <- d_summary %>% 
  filter(metric == 'metric1') %>% 
ggplot() +
  geom_lineribbon(aes(xmin = mean_rep - 1.96 * sd_rep / sqrt(N), xmax = mean_rep + 1.96 * sd_rep / sqrt(N), y = lang, fill = direction, group = direction,), orientation = 'horizontal', alpha =.2) +
  geom_path(aes(x = mean_rep, y = lang, color = direction, group = direction), linewidth = 1.2, alpha = .4) + 
  facet_wrap(cosine ~ dir, ncol = 2) + 
  scale_color_brewer(palette = 'Set1') + 
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = 'Set1') + 
  theme_ggdist() + theme(panel.grid.major = element_line(linewidth=.3))


p3

subtract two groups from each other

d_diff <-
d %>% 
  select(-mean, -sd) %>% 
  pivot_wider(names_from = 'direction', values_from = 'value') %>% 
  mutate(diff = `A  B` - `B  A`)

head(d_diff)
lang cosine metric pass dir B A A B diff
pizza banana 0.85 metric1 1 pizza to other 0.7450953 0.6730020 -0.0720933
pizza banana 0.85 metric1 2 pizza to other 0.7523271 0.7808543 0.0285272
pizza banana 0.85 metric1 3 pizza to other 0.7603078 0.6914059 -0.0689019
pizza banana 0.85 metric1 4 pizza to other 0.8452586 0.7494754 -0.0957832
pizza banana 0.85 metric1 5 pizza to other 0.7355388 0.7503922 0.0148534
pizza banana 0.85 metric1 6 pizza to other 0.8026868 0.8165438 0.0138570 
d_diff_summary <- 
d_diff %>% 
  group_by(lang, cosine, metric) %>% 
  summarise(mean_diff = mean(diff), sd_diff = sd(diff))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'lang', 'cosine'. You can override using
## the `.groups` argument.

plot the difference

d_diff_summary %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, linetype='dashed') +
  geom_segment(aes(x = mean_diff - 1.96 * sd_diff / sqrt(N), xend = mean_diff + 1.96 * sd_diff / sqrt(N), y = lang, yend = lang, color = mean_diff > 0)) +
  geom_point(aes(x = mean_diff, y = lang, color = mean_diff > 0)) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(-.15, .15)) +
  facet_grid(cosine ~ metric) + 
  scale_color_brewer(palette = 'Set1') + xlab('diff') + 
  theme_ggdist() +
  ggtitle("`A  B` - `B  A`")
